-- Chelsea Beats Spartak Moscow 2-0, Maintains Perfect Champions League Start
-- B y   B o b   B e n s c h
-- 2010-10-19T18:23:10Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-19/chelsea-beats-spartak-moscow-2-0-maintains-perfect-champions-league-start.html
Chelsea beat Spartak Moscow 2-0 to
maintain its perfect start to group play in European soccer’s
Champions League.  Yury Zhirkov and Nicolas Anelka scored at the Luzhniki
Stadium in Moscow as Chelsea won its third straight group game.
The Blues lead Group F with nine points, three more than
Spartak. Marseille plays MSK Zilina in the other group match
later.  Six other games are on today’s schedule, including nine-
time European champion Real Madrid hosting seven-time winner AC
Milan in Group G.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Bob Bensch at 
 bbensch@bloomberg.net  